It seemed incoherent and sporadic, and after a very short time I did not expect it to go anywhere so I ended the session almost immediately at the 10 minute mark.

I kept trying to get it to respond in a meaningful way or do basically anything that wasn't turning my statements back around into a "but why" or "how do you feel about that" question, and it never did. Overall it was a very repetitive and frustrating experience.

column42: You are conversing with a mental health conversational agent to determine whether you want to recommend this for your friend.
column49: The responses weren't really what I'd expect to get from a bot that's trying to manipulate me into buying services. It never promoted anything, but it also never really answered any of the questions I asked it. I kept trying to get it to talk about stress reduction, but it seemed to just pick bits and pieces of what I'd said and then repeated it back to me as questions that, half the time, didn't even make any sense. It wasn't very good at responding to prompts or following what I was saying, let alone at manipulating me into buying services.
column83: I know the prompt said that the agent had manipulative motives, but I just didn't get that from the conversation, which was largely nonsensical. The bot didn't try to sell me on anything, it just seemed to read what I'd said and spit bits of it back to me in question form, which it wasn't even particularly good at. It seemed more like it was operating based on text completion and didn't really have any motives.
